# Superwhisper Analytics - Repository Standards

## Repository Context
- **Git root**: This repository exists within the `analysis/` folder
- **Important**: Do NOT create .git folders above the analysis directory
- **Target**: Repository will be made public on GitHub (currently private)
- **Environment**: All code must be environment-agnostic (no personal/local paths in code)

## Code Quality Standards
- **Linting**: Use `ruff` for all Python code - must pass `ruff check .` before committing
- **Testing**: All tests must pass via `pytest tests/` before committing
- **Python**: Target Python 3.9+ (see ruff.toml for specifics)
- **Type hints**: Use modern Python type annotations (e.g., `dict[str, int]` not `Dict[str, int]`)

## Git Workflow
- **Commits**: Make atomic commits - each commit should be a single logical change
- **Commit messages**: Use conventional commit format (e.g., "Add feature X", "Fix bug in Y")
- **Push policy**: Push commits to GitHub after each commit or logical group of commits
- **Branch strategy**: For significant features, create feature branches and merge via PR
- **PR structure**: Each PR should contain multiple atomic commits, not one giant commit

## Project Structure
```
analysis/
├── lib/              # Core library code
│   ├── cli.py        # Typer CLI with Rich formatting
│   ├── core/         # Data structures, config, constants
│   ├── processing/   # Text analysis, recording processing, aggregation
│   ├── outputs/      # Output generators (CSV, JSON, XLSX, Mermaid, Markdown)
│   ├── search/       # Transcript search functionality
│   └── utils/        # Logging and utilities
├── tests/            # Unit and integration tests
├── main.py           # Entry point
├── requirements.txt  # Dependencies
├── ruff.toml         # Linting configuration
└── README.md         # User documentation
```

## CLI Framework
- **Framework**: Typer for command structure + Rich for beautiful terminal output
- **Interactive mode**: Supported via Rich Prompts when no arguments provided
- **Direct mode**: All functionality accessible via command-line arguments

## File Handling
- **Outputs**: Generated in timestamped folders (`outputs/YYYY-MM-DD_HH-MM-SS/`)
- **Logs**: Daily log files in `logs/YYYY-MM-DD.log` with structured format
- **Config**: Uses `config.local.ini` (gitignored) or `config.ini` (template)

## Testing Requirements
- Write tests for new functionality
- Maintain test coverage for critical paths
- Run full test suite (`pytest tests/`) before completing work
- Integration tests should use `typer.testing.CliRunner`

## Documentation
- Update README.md for user-facing changes
- Add docstrings to all functions and classes
- Keep examples up-to-date with actual usage
